      "note": "In view of the fact that the ancient Egyptians worshipped many gods, this observation is not to be taken literally; but since each of the Pharaohs was regarded as an incarnation of the divine principle as such, he claimed and received his people's adoration as their \"Lord All-Highest\" (cf. 79:24), combining within himself, as it were, all the qualities attributable to gods."
